(firstQuint)Colon Staining Efficacy of Single Oral Doses of Methylene Blue MMX.

 Objectives: To describe and evaluate the mucosal staining efficacy of Methylene Blue MMX(R) tablets after total oral doses of 150 or 200 mg in patients undergoing a full colonoscopy for various reasons.

 Primary end-point(s): To evaluate the mucosal staining efficacy of Methylene Blue MMX(R) tablets after total oral doses of 150 or 200 mg.

 Secondary end-point(s): Bowel cleansing quality evaluated according to the validated Boston Bowel Preparation Scale (BBPS) after intake of 150 or 200 mg of Methylene Blue MMX(R) tablets during the intake of the bowel cleansing preparation.

 To collect data about safety and tolerability of Methylene Blue MMX(R) tablets after administration of single oral doses of 150 or 200 mg.

 Methodology: Open label, staining efficacy exploratory study.

